article.description: Glenn Sanabria, who had six 3-pointers, and Rasheem Dunn scored 20 points apiece and St. Francis Brooklyn defeated Mount St. Mary's 81-73 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Sanabria, Dunn lift St. Francis Brooklyn past Mt St. Mary's
article.linkText: Sanabria, Dunn lift St. Francis Brooklyn past Mt St. Mary's
article.story: NEW YORK -- Glenn Sanabria, who had six 3-pointers, and Rasheem Dunn scored 20 points apiece and St. Francis Brooklyn defeated Mount St. Mary's 81-73 on Thursday night. Jalen Jordan added three 3s and 17 points for the Terriers (7-12, 4-3 Northeast Conference), who were 12 of 24 behind the arc and 15 of 16 from the foul line. Junior Robinson had 21 points for the Mountaineers (10-10, 4-3), and Greg Alexander added 16, both hitting four 3s as the team finished 11 of 22 from distance. They were just 1 of 7 in the second half. Alexander had 14 points and Mount St. Mary's made 10 of 15 3-pointers in the first half to open a 44-39 lead. Jordan hit two 3s and Sanabria another as the Terriers scored 13-straight to take a 55-50 lead with 11 1/2 minutes remaining. Robinson twice made it a 2-point game with less than six minutes remaining but down the stretch Dunn made two jumpers and the Terriers went 6 for 6 from the foul line.
